                <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                    <div class="workText">
                        <span class="problem">
                          The world will be short of 12.9 million health-care workers by 2035; today, that figure stands at 7.2 million (WHO 2013). A WHO report released warns that the findings – if not addressed now – will have serious implications for the health of billions of people across all regions of the world.
                          <br><br>
                          Frontline health workers are responsible for up 100 patients and will walk up to 100 mile radius to check-in on patients. Studies have shown that slow information flow......
                        </span>
                        <span class="solution">
                          <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-6">
                              <h4>MIT and SurePod Platform</h4>
                              Sana provides tools and access to innovative technology that make a direct impact on peoples’ well-being. Stop diseases before they start. Vaccines are instrumental in giving a child a shot at life. And enables progressive developmental building.  Many diseases are preventable, including measles, rotavirus, meningitis and pneumonia with immunizations. Expanding access to critical vaccines strengthens our ability to fight disease globally, increase economic stability and keep families healthy here at home. 

                              Spending on services in the early stages of life can bring about benefits such as a growing economy and reduced poverty. Recipients have a better shot at life and contributing to their local economy.   
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1">
                              <h4>Sana Services</h4>
                              Real time two-way communication phones and our connection to our platform can be used by patients, community health workers with lower literacy or limited previous exposure to technology.
                              <br><br>                         
                              <h4>Prenatal and Postnatal Care</h4>
                              Our platform can help patients who don’t know what to do before and after birth.
                              Our system can be used by hospitals and clinical teams to register every pregnancy in their communities and automatically schedule reminders about check-ups. In disaster situations, the SurePod system can report warnings to healthcare workers.

                              Consistent and regular medication reminders is key in managing chronic illnesses, including HIV. Text to voice medication reminders enable treatments to be effective and prevent viruses from rapid mutation.
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </span>
                        <span class="core-technology">
                         Our platform works with limited or no access to internet, and limited access to electricity.

It’s designed for remote and rural areas. Health workers text simple codes to communicate 

information about who’s pregnant, who’s sick, and who’s in need of emergency help. 
<br><br>
The Sanatech infrastructure provides two way communications between mobile devices and 

a web based data store. It is designed to make full use of available data transfer interfaces 

including SMS, WiFi, 3G, GPRS, and even a USB tether between the client and data store. 

This gives Sanatech the flexibility to make best use of available services dependent on 

current conditions and to transfer data even over poor or intermittent networks using an agile 

packetization mechanism. All components of the platform, including the mobile client and 

mobile dispatch server use open source software. Sanatech interfaces with OpenMRS, an open 

source medical record system used around the world, including South Africa, Kenya, Rwanda, 

Mozambique, Haiti, India, China, United States, Pakistan and the Philippines
